8/2/99

  - A bug is found in packetize() when the output buffer happens to fill
    integer number of TPs (ie. has no left over).
  - After fixing this bug, the entire test file can be decoded without problem.

  - Need to test new idea of mixing external and internal routines together
    in a C file!

  - Reset idle time counter after Bufferer Task received demuxStartSema signal
    so that we can obtain more accurate measure of CPU idle time.

  - To obtain DSP idle time measure:
    ((_idleCnterH << 32) + _idleCnterL ) / (_maxCPUload * curTime/100)
    _idleCnter(H,L) is incremented every time idle task is running.
    _maxCPUload is the maximum increment of idle counter in a second.
    curTime is measured in 10 ms clock ticks.

  - Increase PidBuf numbers by increasing the max channel number to 12.
    Code substains longer.  Severe rate reduction still has picture corruption.


