8/16/99
  Overnight run results:

  PPC227: Version 1101
    Die in about 5.9 hrs.
    Trapped in getEsHdr().
    Seems like problem is due to first partial picture parsing.
    Wayne's approach in handling channel start up should be able to
    avoid the problem, because no PicStat for start up TPs will be passed
    to SwitcherTask().

  PPC208: Version 1004
    Die in about 20 hrs.
    Trapped: Output picture is not first in statQue

  Implemented Wayne's new approach for channel initial TP handling.
  => Ver. 1102.  (with RC only)

  Ver. 1103  with CC turned on.

  New channel cleanup mechanism:
    To avoid "Error in cleanupChan()" trap, need to improve channel cleanup.
    Switcher turns the old channel mode to CHAN_RETIRED.
    This will prevent bufferer from putting more TPs to the channel queue.
    After sendVideo() finishes with a picture, check if this is a RETIRED
    channel and we have reached the end of PicStat que.  If so, clean up
    the channel right there,  (in future, also need to check whether audio
    is ready) and change the mode to CHAN_NOT_USED.
    In splice control task, whenever a splice request is received, check
    to see if the corresponding OFF channel is NOT_USED.  If not, simply
    return fail status.

  Ver. 1104 with new channel cleanup mechanism.
  PPC 208: demux 1104  mux 1100  Started 5:02

  Turn on debugPrintf() => Ver. 1105.

  PPC 208: demux 1105, mux 1101, started at 6 pm.

  Future versions:
    1106: higher bufferer priority


