8/23/99

   The real problem is due to insufficient rate reduction.
   This is probably due to the fact that the rate control algorithm
   uses a max quant limit, which depends on the original average quant.
   Unfortunately, the code does not measure actual quant, but set the
   average quant to 8, a small value.  Therefore rate reduction is
   insufficient.  Set to a larger number, such as 24 and retry.

   Failed to make the old rate conversion work for DPI code.


8/24/99
   Develop new, simplified rate conversion rc2.c

   Problem: delay in the feedback from actualRatio to quantScale adjustment
            causing damping in quantScale.  The use of dead zone on ratio
            difference also makes thing worse.

8/25/99
  New rate control seems to make the code run longer.  Bad picture quality.
  Some picture break up.

  Various RC ideas:
  Try adjusting increment instead of scale
    => in general more uniformly distributed degradation
       instead of concentrating around the edge areas.
     
  Increase adjustment value
    => still doesn't help

  Adjust every 16 MBs instead of every MB.  Also measure ratio difference
  of just these 16 MBs instead of the entire picture up to current MB.

  Found a bug in handling skip picture.  Need to retest all the above ideas!

  Stored picStat for each task (switcher, rateconv, output) in diag so they
  can be easily retrieved for debugging.

  Also added a status field in PicStat so we can monitor status of each PicStat.


